Sentencas: A micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell stack model including an integrated cooling system was developed using a quasi three-dimensional, spatially resolved, transient thermodynamic, physical and electrochemical model that accounts for the complex geometrical relations between the cells and cooling-tubes.
Titulo: Evaluation and optimization of a micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell stack model including an integrated cooling system

Sentencas: For the purpose of model evaluation, reference operating, geometrical and material properties are determined.
Titulo: Evaluation and optimization of a micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell stack model including an integrated cooling system

Sentencas: The reference stack design is composed of 3294 cells, with a diameter of 2 mm, and 61 cooling-tubes.
Titulo: Evaluation and optimization of a micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell stack model including an integrated cooling system

Sentencas: The stack is operated at a power density of 300 mW/cm(2) and air is used as the cooling fluid inside the integrated cooling system.
Titulo: Evaluation and optimization of a micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell stack model including an integrated cooling system

Sentencas: Regarding the performance, the reference design achieves an electrical stack efficiency of around 57% and a power output of 1.1 kW.
Titulo: Evaluation and optimization of a micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell stack model including an integrated cooling system

Sentencas: The maximum occurring temperature of the positive electrode electrolyte negative electrode (PEN)-structure is 1369 K.
Titulo: Evaluation and optimization of a micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell stack model including an integrated cooling system

Sentencas: As a result of a design of experiments, parameters of a best-case design are determined.
Titulo: Evaluation and optimization of a micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell stack model including an integrated cooling system

Sentencas: The best-case design achieves a comparable power output of 1.1 kW with an electrical efficiency of 63% and a maximum occurring temperature of the PEN-structure of 1268 K.
Titulo: Evaluation and optimization of a micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell stack model including an integrated cooling system

Sentencas: Nevertheless, the best-case design has an increased volume based on the higher diameter of 3 mm and increased spacing between the cells.
Titulo: Evaluation and optimization of a micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cell stack model including an integrated cooling system
